In [5]:
# MAP

# Create base map object
map_obj= folium.Map(location=[38.9072, -77.0369], zoom_start=13.25,
                   tiles='Stamen Toner')

# Get list of crash locations
locations = df_crashes_2019[['LAT', 'LON']].values

# make the heatmap layer as a feature group using list of crash locations
feature_group1 = FeatureGroup(name="Crashes in 2019")
heatmap = HeatMap((locations), min_opacity=0.2)
heatmap.add_to(feature_group1)

# Add points for camera locations as a feature group, cycling through the camera_locations_list
feature_group2 = FeatureGroup(name="Traffic Cameras")

for point in range(0, len(camera_locations_list)):
    folium.CircleMarker(
        camera_locations_list[point], 
        color='black',
        fill_color="grey", 
        fill_opacity=1, radius='3').add_to(feature_group2)

# Add all feature groups as layers to the map
feature_group1.add_to(map_obj)
feature_group2.add_to(map_obj)

# Add layer controls
LayerControl().add_to(map_obj)

# Load final map
map_obj
